name: FUND OF CHEMICAL PRINCIPLES I
description: Prerequisites: high school math including algebra and trigonometry; chemistry placement examination required.  Introduces the basic concepts of chemistry, including chemical reactions, and bonding, electronic and molecular structure, gases and thermochemistry.  Alternative course to meet the requirement of Chem 125, 126. Emphasis is on mastering the material at the level of the ACS standardized final.

name: GENERAL CHEMISTRY I
description: Prerequisites: At least 620 on the SAT. The first semester of a two-semester sequence in chemistry. Introduces the basic concepts of chemistry, including chemical reactions and bonding, electronic and molecular structure, gases and thermochemistry.
